olive oil
3 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 potato
1 Brown Onion
20 g butter
1 tbs plain flour
1 sachet Sweet Mustard Spice Blend
¼ tsp salt
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 packet chicken breast
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 Kumara
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop garlic. Cut carrot, kumara and potato into bite-sized chunks. Cut onion into wedges.
• Place the butter in a small heatproof bowl and microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.

• Divide carrot, kumara, potato and onion between two lined oven trays. Drizzle with olive oil, then add the melted butter and Aussie spice blend. Season with salt and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the veggies.

• Meanwhile, combine the plain flour, sweet mustard spice blend and the salt in a shallow bowl.
• In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg.
• In a third shallow bowl, place panko breadcrumbs and garlic.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm strips. Coat chicken first in flour mixture, followed by the egg and finally the panko breadcrumbs. Transfer to a plate.

Little cooks: Kids can help crumb the chicken! Use one hand for the wet ingredients and the other for the dry ingredients to avoid sticky fingers.

• When the veggies have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over medium high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken in batches until golden and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

TIP: Add extra oil if needed so the chicken doesn't stick to the pan.

• Add baby spinach leaves to the roasted veggies. Toss to combine and season to taste.

Little cooks: Kids can help wash and toss through the baby spinach!

• Divide spiced roast veggies between plates. Top with sweet mustard crumbed chicken.
• Spoon over dill & parsley mayonnaise to serve. Enjoy!